U.S. benchmarks digest the July breakout, S&P 500 maintains first support
U.S. stocks are lower early Monday, pressured ahead of a full quarterly earnings calendar, and the Federal Reserve’s latest policy directive, due out Wednesday.  Against this backdrop, each major U.S. benchmark continues to digest the July rally to previously uncharted territory. 

Jul. 24, 2017 at 11:52 a.m. ET
by Michael Ashbaugh










